        "title": "Nursing burnout during COVID-19: A systematic review and meta-analysis of prevalence and risk factors",
        "abstract": "Background: The COVID-19 pandemic significantly increased workload and psychological burden on nurses. Objectives: To estimate the global prevalence of burnout among nurses during the COVID-19 pandemic and identify associated risk factors. Methods: Systematic review with meta-analysis following PRISMA guidelines. Data sources: PubMed, CINAHL, and Embase (January 2020 to December 2022). Results: 45 studies (n=28,432 nurses) were included. Pooled prevalence of burnout was 41.8% (95% CI: 36.2-47.5). Female sex, ICU work, and lack of PPE were significant risk factors.",
